    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Fender Mounted Cross View Mirrors</title>
        <para>Fender-mounted mirror assemblies are mounted on the forward section of the fender assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006152">Figure 152, Item 2</hotlnk>) with a lateral mounting brace attached to the side
            of the hood section. The mirror assemblies are bolted to the hood and fender assemblies.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006152" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006152.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 152. Fender-Mounted Mirror (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. MIRROR / FENDER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MIRROR HEAD</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MIRROR / HOOD SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MIRROR MOUNTING BASE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>5. MIRROR MAIN SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the hood and fender assembly forward to access the mounting bolts for the nuts and flat
                washers.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>An assistant should be available to steady mirror assembly during removal to prevent damage or
                        breaking of the assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006153" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006153.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 153. Fender Mounted Mirror Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. MIRROR / FENDER BRACKET MOUNTING BOLT, WASHER AND NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MIRROR BASE MOUNTING BOLTS, NUTS AND WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MIRROR BASE FENDER REINFORCING PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEATED MIRROR HARNESS OPENING (IF EQUIPPED)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FENDER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the lock nut and flat washer on the underside of the fender section. Secure the lock
                nut and flat washer and loosen (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006153">Figure 153, Item 2</hotlnk>) the mounting bolts in the mounting bracket on
                the outside fender section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the lock nut and washer on the inside vertical section of the hood assembly. Loosen
                the mounting bolt in the lateral bracket base (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006153">Figure 153, Item 1</hotlnk>). It would be advisable to have an assistant
                steady the mirror during the removal process and to prevent breakage if the mirror should fall.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mirror assembly and brackets.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant supporting the mirror base and mirror head, loosen and remove the
                attachment nuts and washers from the mirror mounting reinforcing plate on the underside of the fender
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006154" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006154.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 154. Mirror Mounting and Support Brackets</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BRACKET MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MIRROR SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MIRROR MAIN SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MAIN SUPPORT ATTACHMENT CLAMPS</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LATERAL MIRROR SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>6. MIRROR BASE ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. MIRROR BASE MOUNTING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>8. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>9. MIRROR / FENDER MOUNTED BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>10. HOOD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure to remove the opposite side mirror assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
